name: Stacy Jorgensen
introduction: Originally from DeLand, Florida, Stacy moved to Los Angeles at the age of 17 to attend The University of Southern California, where she majored in Theatre and minored in Cinema.  While at USC, she began studying at the Groundlings, and continued on through the Performance Lab. Some of her acting jobs have included an episode of CSI, a supporting role in the film Lovely and Amazing, and supporting roles in independent films such as The Steamroom, and Stellina Blue.  Stacy also starred in and co-produced two short films, Back From Reality, and True Love Never Dies.Stacy starred in and produced the sci-fi/horror feature film, Grey Skies.  She also had a supporting role on CBS's Criminal Minds,  as well as being a part of short films including Cupcake, Botes al Amanecer (Official Selection of the 2012 Cannes Film Festival), Tryouts, and she produced the Sopranos-esque webseries, The Pacellis.
